-- Pimco total return fund fell 0.8 pct in Dec-prelim Morningstar data
-- By Luciana Lopez and Sam Forgione
-- Wed Dec 31, 2014 08:53AM EST
-- None



NEW YORK, Dec 31 (Reuters) - The Pimco Total Return Fund, the world's largest bond fund, fell 0.8 percent in December to trail 95 percent of its peers, preliminary Morningstar data showed on Wednesday.

The fund rose 4.36 percent for the year, trailing 77 percent of peers. The Pimco Total Return Exchange-Traded Fund's <BOND.P> net asset value fell 0.22 percent in the month, trailing 61 percent of peers, the data showed. But the ETF's net asset value rose 6.7 percent for the year, putting it in the top percentile of its peer group.